			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Spell Set Up For Swarming<a name="26084"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 8 04 7:53 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>1-3 DoTs
<br />
4 Fulfil's DoT (inc MR debuff)
<br />
5 Song of Travel
<br />
6 Mezz
<br />
7 Selo's / Replenishment
<br />
8 Charm
<br />

<br />
You only really need 6 slots for swarming - 4 DoTs, charm, and invis if you don't have a clicky.
<br />

<br />
I just keep mezz and standard selos up to help me if things go bad, someone nearby needs help, or just simply to leave my swarming mid-run. Sometimes I'll have replenishment up instead of selos, if I think I might need it - but this is rare.
<br />

<br />
I tend to chant down with just 3 DoTs - this means they're almost on 100% due to the build-in debuff, whereas with 4 it just takes a missed note and then you can get resists. I guess this is a factor of your level vs the mobs you fight though.
<br />

<br />
I use fulfil's to debuff MR but should probably update this to oos now ;)
<br />

<br />
The order may seem strange, but this helps fit in with my setup on other songs and I arrange hotkeys in a manner that makes it easy to twist the groups of songs I need.
<br />
</span></td>
