			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Spell Set Up For Swarming<a name="26105"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 8 04 9:39 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>1 - Selo's v 2.5
<br />
2-5 Various DoTs depends on zone (i.e. if fire resist high, replace with Fufils)
<br />
6 - Largo's (make sure you are facing any runners at 20% and lower and if possible, get in close)
<br />
7 - Forage
<br />
8 - Tracking
<br />
9 - Charm
<br />
0 - Cancel Magic
<br />

<br />
All above linked to number pad.
<br />

<br />
I'm currently 59 and very close to 60. Charm rarely works in the zones I kite in, but occasionally I get one to stick. Usually it is an add to my kite mess that already has some serious aggro on me. So if I can charm, I will Largo one of the MoB's and sick pet on it. Any members of the swarm who do not hate me quite as much may turn on my charmed pet. I keep DoTting the one MoB keeping my pet in my Switch-Target memory (set to the enter key on my number pad btw). Should my pet be getting close to expiration, hit enter, hit 0 and send a DoT to finish the job.
<br />

<br />
Just my 2cp worth.
<br />

<br />
Wila from Torv.</span></td>
