				<td colspan="2"><span>At 51 I am set up like this for swarming:
<br />

<br />
1-4 chants (will sometimes swap fufil's in slot 1 if I am fighting mobs with a high resist rate on one of the standard 4 chants (fire, cold, poison, disease)
<br />
5 - Snare/slow
<br />
6 - Accelerating chorus
<br />
7 - Song of travel
<br />
8 - Charm
<br />

<br />
I made the switch from invis to song of travel for breaking charm since I bought run3.  I also am practicing using flute when charming to get used to it.  
<br />

<br />
I also use the snare to 'lock down' singles when they are crossing the 20% life threshhold, combined with me sitting on top of them to try and minimize 'poofing'.  Snare also is somewhat effective if I accidentally charm the wrong mob; snare does wonders convincing a mob mad at me for charming it to turn and fight the one chewing it up from behind.
<br />

<br />
Badji
<br />
51 Minstril
<br />
ARO</span></td>
